<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=85410><img src=http://personal.atl.bellsouth.net/lig/j/a/jaysen2/Wess-sig2.jpg></a></html></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wessley>Wessley</A> at: 3/4/02 2:30:30 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dalninil>Dalninil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 207<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/4/02 5:00:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1483.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards not good in exp grind?</span><hr size=1> Solo ing with a cleric isn't that hard, you just have to think about what you're going to hunt. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 622<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/4/02 5:08:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1483.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Wizard AE is nice ..</span><hr size=1> .. if you have an enc and you have a couple wizards.  A single wizard is basically a null-value add to an xp group at upper levels, though.  When pulling 50+ for a group, if the group adds a wizard, I can't pull any faster or any more than before.  Add a rogue or ranger or mage or necro or .. well, most anyone else .. and I can pull faster; ie. wizards are basically an xp-sink in an xp group.  A wizard gets maybe 1 cast per mob or he'll go OOM really quick.  This makes for a boring job.  Basically, need to sit about doing not much of anything but keeping attention focused so you can rescue the group with a heavy burn or evac.<br>
<br>
This is one of the reasons I gave up on wizards long before Kunark came out.  Wizards have improved a lot since then as a class, but unless you have one of the uber clickable DD items, pull-rate doesn't go up.  Wizards are the group's safety-net, not a group's damage class.  They're around for when the shit hits the fan and you need to shout, &quot;Help me Mr. Wizard!&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udeffhead01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deffhead01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Gnevil Mastermind</span><br>  Posts: 171<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/4/02 7:08:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1483.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Clerics solo?</span><hr size=1> Since some people seems to think that solo'ing with a Cleric aint all that hard, I'd very much like some advice as how to go about this.<br>
I have only played a Necromancer and Shaman before, so I am still pretty clueless as how to solo effectively with a Cleric.<br>
Any advice is appreciated! :)<br>
<br>
/Tanheuser Finkelstein <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 629<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/4/02 7:13:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1483.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> /tell warrior need a group?</span><hr size=1> That one works well.  The other way is to find undead and kill them.  You're basically like a souped up paladin when it comes to killing undead solo.  I had a cleric friend that used to solo to catch up to everyone.  He did the entire undead tour: unrest, guk, feerot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/unooneofnote.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NoOneOfNote</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/4/02 7:41:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1483.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Some Replies</span><hr size=1> <br>
Heh, didn't figure on making many friends with this, but since i'd been agonizing over my own character choice I thought i'd write it anyway.<br>
<br>
As for those who say, `just pick something you like', that's not bad advice. However there are a number of classes I would like to play. And I think it's worth considering how well these fit into the server environment. No matter how much you like your class LFG is boring. And you can't roleplay much while soloing or LFG.<br>
<br>
I should have been more clear about what `soloists' meant. It wasn't an insult to the soloing ability of bards, shaman and such. It meant more that the pet classes are designed *primarily* to be soloists. As a result they solo well and might not be the most desirable thing in groups.<br>
<br>
I said a ranger gives up any pretensions of tanking... i.e. is not a very good tank.<br>
<br>
As for Wizards. No, i've never seen an AoE group doing XP grinding. Perhaps it's common in the higher level zones but it needs such a careful selection of classes that I can't believe it's that common. In any case, as with wizard soloing, you need to be a decent level (read have a decent snare and AoE) before it's going to work.<br>
<br>
As for melee grind groups I have no doubt wizards have problems. They are constrained in how much damage they can deliver by the amount of mana they have and the amount of agro they generate. Over a long period mana limits the damage they do. Over a short period agro limits the damage they do. A rogue (my main) has neither of these problems. <br>
<br>
Their AoE attacks are massively efficient, but outside of the fabled AoE groups, tends to interfere with crowd control and get the wizard (and party) killed.<br>
<br>
Perhaps I am completely wrong with wizards, i'm almost tempted to play one to find out, in which case you can continue to laugh at my ignorance and profit from their being one less wizard.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukaludramaderlas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaludram Aderlas</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.fortunecity.com/samslade/shadcon/Images/minisc.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dark Lord of Troublemaking</span><br>  Posts: 150<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/5/02 1:34:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1483.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Some Replies</span><hr size=1> Lorec, shamans are the worst solo of the traditionally accepted classes that solo.  Those classes being Necro, Magus, Druid, Wizard, and Shaman.  The problem with thise comparison is that gear and player competency play a major factor.  Whilst druids and wizards can multi-kite, Necros can rot like no others.  A 49 necro can camp all 3 IGs in EF at once.  You will not see this of any of the others.  I admit it is hard to say who is the best of them, but I think it is obvious that the shaman and the magus are on the bottom of that heap post 49. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/unooneofnote.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NoOneOfNote</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/5/02 4:31:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1483.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Some Replies</span><hr size=1> <br>
As I understand it shaman are considered a strong soloist in that they can take down quite tough monsters in a wide variety of situations. With slow, pet, SoW and powerful dot they can reverse-kite and rot some impressively tough MOB's. And with the ability to regenerate and convert health to mana they can be good to go very quickly. And rotting, or even tanking a slowed mob, works well indoors.<br>
<br>
However against ideal mobs / situations the quad kiters can probably generate more XP over time. And the pet users can probably harvest more low blues over the same time. Oh, and the shaman matures pretty late (34+).<br>
<br>
However, shaman are perhaps the most versatile class. The second best healers in the game, good buffs, excellent slows, powerful DOT and average pet can bring a lot to a group. Whereas the specialist soloists are a bit more problematic.<br>
<br>
I'd be playing one in a second if I didn't already have one (as part of a dungeon exploration duo) on another server.<br>
<br>
But then I play a rogue as main on that other server. And they can make a solid claim to being the *worst* soloists in the entire game...so i'm basically jealous of everyone elses massive ability to solo <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uieglios.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ieglios</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/5/02 5:01:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1483.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Some Replies</span><hr size=1> I have a different perspective and that is the class is not as important as the player playing it. You can be a necro and just plain suck, or you can be a paladin and really do well. Through in a low end average equipment into the mix and only the really good players or organized guilds fall into those little neat boxes on this server.<br>
 Knowing how to play your class and what your role is in the group is much more important than which class you choose, I say play what you want to roleplay and go with it, you will find those like me who will appreciate your effort and your sacrifice of power for play. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubelrosian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Belrosian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/5/02 7:03:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1483.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://strider.xoasis.com/belrosian.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Some Replies</span><hr size=1> For all the levels below 50, a wizard can easily cast 1 or 2 times per fight without straining his mana. And those 1 or 2 casts will do at least one sixth of the total damage. Anyone who says wizards are experience sinks is biased. It is attitudes like this which make the wizard's life tedius. <p><i>I must admit when we first pulled that avocet last night I thought I was a gonner. I hit and hit and hit and his health did not go down. Twice the cleric healed me from below half and then you nuked him twice and bam he started running.  I then breathed a sigh of relief. </i></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubelrosian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Belrosian</A> at: 3/5/02 7:06:31 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uartillis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Artillis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 309<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/5/02 7:17:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1483.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Some Replies</span><hr size=1> Bjond hit the nail on the head with a wizards one, and in my opinion, ONLY flaw.  They can't keep up well in FAST grind EXP groups.  I have grouped in EXP groups and done fine but when they started pulling very fast I started falling behind and had to med thru some pulls.  Now EXP grinds are very common on a regular blue server and seem to make up about the majority of the game tell you get to raid levels.  Raids are one of the few things wizards excel in and come into their own at 50+.  But like I mentioned if the standard uber fast pull EXP grind is the only thing that wizards suck at (desides AE groups) then they should be fine on this server.  <br>
<br>
On a side note I was in an EXP grind group (not an AE one) in DL on other server were we had 3 wizards one mage a druid and a shadow knight and we were killing stuff faster then many of the groups around us becase the thing would drop dead before the shadow knight could even get it back to the group, each wizard, the mage, and the druid, would nuke once = dead creature.  If we had an enchanter we could have gone even faster.  Sad thing was the shadow knight was so biased and anal about casters that he left our group and said &quot;I'm going to go somewere were I feel needed&quot;.  He didn't like using different tactics from a &quot;standard&quot; fast pull EXP group even thought we were netting just as much exp.<br>
<br>
Ok not going to post again concerning this, hehe.  I'm kind of a fanatic when it comes to defending my favorite class <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/unooneofnote.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NoOneOfNote</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/5/02 7:21:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1483.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Player over class</span><hr size=1> <br>
Yes and No. A good player is a fantastic asset. They'll maximize their own classes abilities and they'll do everything they can to work with the party and make it stronger. They're also a lot more fun to game with even if there class might not be optimal. They might even teach me something I didn't know, like how wizard AoE groups rock <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
And what ever class I pick I will do my absolute best to play it well. That's a given. But even the very best player can't change the powers of the class. He can't make up for the fact that his class might not be what parties want and need.<br>
<br>
I'm not saying i'd use this as a basis for rejecting others. But when *I* am looking for a group I would like to be playing a character that people are glad to see in addition to a gamer that they're happy to game with.<br>
<br>
Of course I do tend to over-analyse things.<br>
<br>
